# Keeps the build context lean for repo-root-context builds (deploy/api.Dockerfile's
# `api` service and docker/Dockerfile's `claude-code:base`, both of which COPY from
# the repo root as of #601). Docker tars up and sends the whole context to the daemon
# before evaluating a single COPY, so an untrimmed context here means shipping
# frontend's ~150MB node_modules and local .NET build output on every build for images
# that need neither — frontend has its own separate build context (the `frontend`
# service's `context: ./frontend`), unaffected by this file.
#
# Patterns are unanchored (match at any depth), same as .gitignore — bin/ and obj/
# below also cover shim/bin/ and shim/obj/.
.git/
bin/
obj/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
.lyric/
.lyric-*/
.claude/
